# LLM Patterns

## Purpose
Use LLM capabilities intentionally and keep model-dependent behavior constrained.

## Requirements
- use deterministic code when it is sufficient
- isolate prompt text from business logic
- make context assembly explicit
- prefer structured output contracts
- define tool use and fallback behavior clearly
- keep retrieval preparation separate from answer formatting
- bound model responsibilities so contracts remain testable
- record assumptions when prompts depend on hidden or inferred context

## Apply When
- designing prompts
- building context-packing logic
- integrating model outputs into application code
